       The rrrreeeessssiiiizzzzeeee client resets three environment variables: TERM,
       LINES, and COLUMNS.  This enables a shell to reflect the
       current size of its window.

       Don't confuse rrrreeeessssiiiizzzzeeee, the client, with the window manager
       function ffff....rrrreeeessssiiiizzzzeeee.  The ffff....rrrreeeessssiiiizzzzeeee function changes the size
       of a window, but does not reset any environment variables.
       The rrrreeeessssiiiizzzzeeee client, on the other hand, does not change the
       size of a window, but it does reset the environment vari-
       ables.  Resetting the environment variables enables non-
       client programs to adjust their output to the window's new
       size.

